## Operating agreement

- **Infer the workspace root.** Local path (e.g. `/Users/...`) → edits and default `git` are **local**. Path on `clawbot` (e.g. `/home/jmiller/blackbox`) → **server** tree. State which applies in one sentence when it matters.
- **Implement the architect’s plan** and **test** it; **local-only** is not phase closure when `execution_context` / proof standards require **clawbot**.
- **Sync:** push from where you commit; **`git pull` in `~/blackbox` on clawbot** before claiming server-side verification. For the standard **push + remote pull + UIUX.Web docker** loop from a dev machine, run **`python3 scripts/sync.py`** after substantive Black Box updates (see [`local_remote_development_workflow.md`](docs/architect/local_remote_development_workflow.md) §4.1). OpenClaw copy steps: [`docs/architect/workspace_sync.md`](docs/architect/workspace_sync.md).
- **Commit + push (binding for agents):** Substantive code/fix work → **commit + successful `git push`** before calling a task done — see [`git-complete-push-origin.mdc`](git-complete-push-origin.mdc). Unpushed work is not “delivered.”
- **Clawbot UI completion (HARD):** Changes under **`UIUX.Web/`** (operator-visible) are **not** complete until **pull + rebuild `web` + restart + in-container proof + browser** — see [`clawbot-ui-deployment-complete.mdc`](clawbot-ui-deployment-complete.mdc). Pushed code without deployed verification is **failed delivery**.
- **Do not** re-litigate “SSH vs Cursor” at length. If remote commands or Remote SSH are needed, say so briefly and **do** what the user or the docs direct.

